Package com.hypirion.io

Class Summary
ClosingPipe A ClosingPipe is a link between an input stream and an output stream or a reader or writer: The pipe, once started, will asynchronously redirect all data received from the input source to the output source until it is paused, stopped or the input source is empty.
Pipe A Pipe is a link between an input stream and an output stream or a reader or writer: The pipe, once started, will asynchronously redirect all data received from the input source to the output source until it is paused, stopped or the input source is empty.
RevivableInputStream A revivable input stream is an unbuffered input stream wrapping another input stream.
